$ cquad4_constrained_thermal.bdf
$ Single CQUAD4 — uniaxial constrained thermal stress (x-direction)
$
$ Geometry: 1 m × 1 m square plate, t = 0.1 m
$ Material: E = 1e6 Pa, nu = 0.3, alpha = 1e-5 /°C
$ Load:     uniform T = 100 °C (ΔT = 100 °C, T_ref = 0)
$ BCs:      fix T1 of ALL four nodes — plate cannot expand in x
$           fix T2 of node 1 — prevents y rigid-body translation and rotation
$           Plate is free to contract/expand in y (Poisson effect)
$
$ Hand calculation (plane stress, x fully constrained, y free → σ_y = 0):
$   ε_x = 0  (kinematically enforced)
$   σ_y = 0  (free lateral surface)
$   From plane-stress Hooke with thermal strain:
$     ε_x = (σ_x - ν*σ_y) / E + α*ΔT = 0
$     → σ_x = -E*α*ΔT = -1e6 * 1e-5 * 100 = -1000 Pa  (compressive)
$
$   von Mises = |σ_x| = 1000 Pa  (σ_y = σ_xy = 0)
$
SOL 101
CEND
SUBCASE 1
  LABEL = CQUAD4 CONSTRAINED THERMAL
  LOAD = 1
  SPC = 1
  DISPLACEMENT = ALL
  STRESS = ALL
BEGIN BULK
PARAM,CSVOUT,YES
GRID,1,,0.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,2,,1.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,3,,1.0,1.0,0.0
GRID,4,,0.0,1.0,0.0
MAT1,1,1.0E6,,0.3,0.0,1.0E-5,0.0
PSHELL,1,1,0.1
CQUAD4,1,1,1,2,3,4
$ Fix T1 (x) of all nodes — prevents x-expansion, creates thermal stress in x
SPC1,1,1,1
SPC1,1,1,2
SPC1,1,1,3
SPC1,1,1,4
$ Fix T2 (y) of node 1 — prevents y rigid-body translation
$ Fix T2 (y) of node 2 — prevents rotation about z
SPC1,1,2,1
SPC1,1,2,2
$ Uniform temperature T = 100 °C
TEMP,1,1,100.0
TEMP,1,2,100.0
TEMP,1,3,100.0
TEMP,1,4,100.0
ENDDATA
